plot: Del tries his hand at being a showbiz manager, and one of his clients is his 3-months pregnant girlfriend Raquel. But will things go to plan?

Rodney has lost his home, his wife, his job and his career - and Raquel is now 3 months' pregnant. The Trotters are hoping their luck will change, and when Del hears that the local cabaret club will pay a premium if he can provide a singer for the night, he sees Raquel as the perfect solution. Contracts are signed - the only problem seems to be there's only 24 hours to rehearse, and Raquel has no band, no material and, worst of all, stage fright!—stevecann2003
